  "clinicalPearl": "Empyema is FAILED PNEUMONIA with compartmentalized pus and surgical potential. AMEXAN must: detect antibiotic failure early, identify loculation via ultrasound, drain promptly, and escalate to surgery if no response within 48–72 hours. Pus in the pleural space = drainage mandatory."
